#
# ---- HAND-DIAGNOSIS KEY (cover this before you read it) ----
# TRUE ROOT CAUSE: the model server was OOM-killed (TWICE, then crash-looping)
#   because an FP16 7B (~14-16GB) plus a KV cache pre-allocated for context=32768
#   batch=4 did not fit in RAM. Subsystem: MEMORY / sizing.
# OFFENDING LINE: "Out of memory: Killed process 8423 (ollama) ... anon-rss:15994208kB"
# RED HERRINGS (an AI may wrongly seize on these): the nvme0n1 I/O timeout
#   (it RETRY-SUCCEEDED — not the cause); the USB device add; the latency WARN;
#   the apt upgrade (coincidental timing). Note the SECOND OOM (PID 8590) — this
#   is a crash loop; "restart" is the wrong fix. Fix = quantize + smaller context,
#   or add RAM, plus a MemoryMax cap so it fails predictably.
